Israel not planning to hold direct talks with Lebanon






                Israeli Foreign Minister Gideon Saar said on Sunday that Israel was not planning to hold direct talks with Lebanon in the coming days and had not told the United States it was running low on missile interceptors.

Israel's Haaretz newspaper reported on Saturday that Israel and Lebanon were expected to&nbsp;hold direct talks&nbsp;in the coming days.&nbsp;
